                           The Councel with whom the Committee did Adviſe, touching the ſaid BILL, were principally theſe, viz. They had, firſt of all, in ſome Eſſential Parts of the BILL, the Opinion of Sir George Treby, late Recorder of the City of London, Attorney-General, and now Lord Chief Juſtice of the Common-Pleas; The preſent Attorney-General Ja. Ward; Sir Bartholomew Shower;
Sir Salathiel Lovell the preſent Recorder; Sir Francis Pemberton;
Mr. Common Sergeant; and others of the City-Councel.
